pan=1|2003\n|''None''\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 0\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2005\n|{{vb|VIE}}\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 1\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2007\n|{{vb|MDV}}\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 1\n|- \n|rowspan=2|2009\n|{{vb|LIB}}\n|rowspan=2 align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{vb|MYA}}\n|- \n|rowspan=2|2011\n|{{vb|AFG}}\n|rowspan=2 align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{vb|TKM}}\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2013\n|{{vb|OMA}}\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 1\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2015\n|''None''\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 0\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2017\n|''None''\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 0\n|- \n|rowspan=1|2019\n|''None''\n|rowspan=1 align=center| 0\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Awards==\n{{main|Asian Men's Volleyball Championship Best Players||Asian Men's Volleyball Championship Most Valuable Player}}\nAt the end of each Championship, awards are presented to the players and teams for accomplishments other than their final team positions in the tournament. There are currently six awards:\n*The ''Most Valuable Player'' for the best player, determined by a vote of organizing committees.\n*The ''Best Opposite spiker'' for the best opposite spiker, determined by their statistics and a vote of organizing committees.\n*The ''Best Outside spikers'' for the best outside spikers, determined by their statistics and a vote of organizing committees.\n*The ''Best Middle blocker'' for the best middle blockers, determined by their statistics and a vote of organizing committees.\n*The ''Best Setter'' for the best setter, determined by their statistics and a vote of organizing committees.\n*The ''Best Libero'' for the best libero, determined by their statistics and a vote of organizing committees.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Volleyball|Sports|Asia}}\n* [[Asian Women's Volleyball Championship]]\n* [[Volleyball at the Asian Games]]\n* [[AVC Cup for Men]]\n* [[Asian Men's U23 Volleyball Championship]]\n* [[Asian Men's U20 Volleyball Championship]]\n* [[Asian Boys' U19 Volleyball Championship]]\n\n==References==\n* [http://sports123.com/vol/index.html Sports123.com]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.asianvolleyball.net/ Official AVC website]\n\n{{Volleyball Asian Championship}}\n{{Volleyball}}\n{{International volleyball (Men)}}\n{{Asian Championships}}\n{{Oceanian Championships}}\n\n[[Category:Asian volleyball championships| ]]\n[[Category:Asian volleyball championships men's competitions| ]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1975|V]]\n[[Category:Asian championships|Volleyball]]\n[[Category:International volleyball competitions]]\n[[Category:International men's volleyball competitions]]\n[[Category:Volleyball in Asia]]\n[[Category:Biennial sporting events]]\n[[Category:Asian Volleyball Confederation]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the men's indoor volleyball tournament|the men's tournament|Asian Women's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{short description|indoor volleyball competition for men's national teams}}\n{{Infobox sports league\n| logo           = \n| pixels         =\n| sport          = Volleyball\n| founded        = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1975}}\n| inaugural      = [[1975 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|1975]]\n| teams          = 16 (finals)<br>65 (eligible to enter qualification)\n| continent      = [[Asia]] and [[Oceania]] ([[Asian Volleyball Confederation|AVC]])\n| champion       = {{vb|IRI}} (3rd title) \n| most_champs    = {{vbw|JPN}} (9 titles)\n| TV             = SMMTV\n| website        = {{nowrap|[http://asianvolleyball.net Asian Volleyball Confederation]}}\n| upcoming_season = 2021 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship\n}}\nThe '''Asian Men's Volleyball Championship''' is an international [[volleyball]] competition in [[Asia]] and [[Oceania]] contested by the senior men's national teams of the members of [[Asian Volleyball Confederation]] (AVC), the sport's continent governing body. The initial gap between championships was four years, but since [[1987 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|1987]] they have been awarded every two years. The current champion is [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran]], which won its third title at the [[2019 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2019 tournament]].\n\nThe 20 Asian Championship tournaments have been won by five different national teams. [[Japan men's national volleyball team|Japan]] have won nine times. The other Asian Championship winners are [[South Korea men's national volleyball team|South Korea]], with four titles; [[China men's national volleyball team|China]] with three titles; [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran]] with three titles; and [[Australia men's national volleyball team|Australia]], with one title.\n\nThe [[2019 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2019 Asian Championship]] took place in Tehran, Iran.\n\n==Results summary==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; width: 100%; text-align: center;\"\n|- bgcolor=#c1d8ff\n!rowspan=2 width=6%|Year\n!rowspan=2 width=12%|Host\n!width=1% rowspan=23 bgcolor=ffffff|\n!colspan=3|Final\n!width=1% rowspan=23 bgcolor=ffffff|\n!colspan=3|Third place match\n!width=1% rowspan=25 bgcolor=#ffffff|\n!rowspan=2 width=5%|Teams\n|- bgcolor=#efefef\n!width=14%|Champions\n!width=9%|Score\n!width=14%|Runners-up\n!width=14%|3rd place\n!width=9%|Score\n!width=14%|4th place\n|-\n|1975<br />[[1975 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Details]]\n|{{flagicon|AUS}}<br>[[Melbourne]]\n|'''{{vb-big|JPN|1947}}'''\n|[[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]]\n|{{vb-big|KOR|1949}}\n|{{vb-big|CHN}}\n|[[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]]\n|{{vb-big|AUS}}\n|7\n|- bgcolor=#E8E8F0\n|1979<br />[[1979 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Details]]\n|{{flagicon|BHR|1972}}<br>[[Manama]]\n|'''{{vb-big|CHN}}'''\n|[[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]]\n|{{vb-big|KOR|1949}}\n|{{vb-big|JPN|1947}}\n|[[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]]\n|{{vb-big|AUS}}\n|15\n|-\n|1983<br />[[1983 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Details]]\n|{{flagicon|JPN|1947}}<br>[[Tokyo]]\n|'''{{vb-big|JPN|1947}}'''\n|[[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]]\n|{{vb-big|CHN}}\n|{{vb-big|KOR|1949}}\n|[[Round-robin 