ekhanaIsNotSuicide |quote={{PD-notice}} }}\n* {{citation |last=Um\u0101sv\u0101ti |first= Umaswami |title=That which is (Translator: Nathmal Tatia) |url={{Google books|0Rw4RwN9Q1kC|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |year=1994 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-0-06-068985-8 }}\n* {{citation |last=Vallely |first=Anne |title=Guardians of the Transcendent: An Ethnology of a Jain Ascetic Community |url={{Google books|eI4PAY9rDmQC|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |date=2002 |publisher=University of Toronto Press |isbn=978-0-8020-8415-6 }}\n* {{citation |last=von Glasenapp |first=Helmuth |authorlink=Helmuth von Glasenapp |others=[[Shridhar B. Shrotri]] (trans.) |title=Jainism: An Indian Religion of Salvation |trans-title=Der Jainismus: Eine Indische Erlosungsreligion |url={{Google books|WzEzXDk0v6sC|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass]] (Reprint: 1999) |year=1925| location=Delhi |isbn=978-81-208-1376-2 }}\n* {{citation |last=Voorst |first=Robert E. Van |authorlink=Robert E. Van Voorst |title=RELG: World |url={{Google books|37TcBAAAQBAJ|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |publisher=Cengage Learning |year=2015 |edition=Second |isbn=978-1-285-43468-1 }}\n* {{citation |last=Wiley |first=Kristi L. |authorlink=Kriti L. Wiley |title=The A to Z of Jainism |url={{Google books|cIhCCwAAQBAJ|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |year=2009 | volume=38 |publisher=Scarecrow |isbn=978-0-8108-6337-8 }}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|first=Kristi L.|last= Wiley|title=Historical Dictionary of Jainism|url={{Google books|QCT-CQAAQBAJ|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}}|year=2004| publisher=Scarecrow|isbn=978-0-8108-6558-7}}\n* {{citation |last=Williams |first=Robert |title=Jaina Yoga: A Survey of the Mediaeval \u015ar\u0101vak\u0101c\u0101ras |url={{Google books|LLKcrIJ6oscC|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |year=1991 |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass]] |isbn=978-81-208-0775-4 }}\n* {{citation| last=Winternitz| first=Moriz|authorlink=Moriz Winter